-- China's Energy Use by High-Usage Industries Is `Under Control,' Zhu Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-28T02:33:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/china-s-energy-use-by-high-usage-industries-is-under-control-zhu-says.html
Energy use by China’s high-consuming
industries is “under control,” Zhu Hongren, the Ministry of
Industry and Information Technology’s chief engineer, said at a
briefing in Beijing today.  China’s energy consumption growth in most regions is
slowing, Zhu said. Third-quarter energy use per unit of
industrial output fell “noticeably,” Zhu said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
